class Solution {
    public int[] sumEvenAfterQueries(int[] A, int[][] queries) {
        int S = 0;
        for (int x: A) {
            if (x % 2 == 0) {
                S += x;
            }
        }

        int[] ans = new int[queries.length];

        for (int i = 0; i < queries.length; ++i) {
            int val = queries[i][0], index = queries[i][1];
            if (A[index] % 2 == 0) {
                S -= A[index];
            }
            A[index] += val;
            if (A[index] % 2 == 0) {
                S += A[index];
            }
            ans[i] = S;
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
```

This class defines a method `sumEvenAfterQueries` which takes an integer array `A` and a 2D integer array `queries`. The method updates the array `A` according to the queries and returns an array of results where each result is the sum of even values in `A` after each query.
